CatDescriptText: William Dunbar, 1718 Bedford Avenue and Elliott Matthews, 1604 Colwell Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "In the coming November elections, do you think voters should elect another Democratic Governor or change to a Republican?" William Dunbar's answer reads: "They should elect another Democratic Governor. The reason is that I think that Negroes have gained more in city and state governments under the Democrats than the Republicans."  Elliott Matthews' answer reads: "I think they should stay with the Democrats.  The reason is that I've never gone hungry under the Democrats, but I have under the Republicans."
TitMainTitle: William Dunbar and Elliott Matthews, wearing Mt. Nebo fezzes and ribbons inscribed "MEMBER Mt. Nebo..." and "Imperial Grand Council A.A.O.N.M.S. U.S. & Canada... SESSION Aug. 10-16, 1958 Pittsburgh, PA," standing in front of stone wall
